text.__SUMMARY__: Schefflera morototoni (yagrumo macho; syn. Didymopanax morototoni (Aubl.) Decne. & Planch., Didymopanax morototoni var. angustipetalum March; Panax morototoni Aublet; Sciadophyllum paniculatum Britton ) is a timber tree  native to southern Mexico, the Greater Antilles, Central America, and South America.  It grows in a variety of habitats, such as the Caatinga, Cerrado, and Amazon Rainforest of Brazil.
